<h2 id="section-top">Haematology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=149">Taunton and Somerset NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>01823 34 (2271, 2294, 2269)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent57ed6b8e18a84a5eab9625590023159e">
</div>
<div class="bodyHeading">
<div>
<div class="mainHeading">Haematology, Oncology and Palliative Care (HOPE)</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pageWysiwygBlock grid_6 mceContentBody">
<div class="Normal LabelEditOverClassML" id="dnn_ctr2437_HtmlModule_lblContent">
<div>The cancer services department provides a comprehensive clinical service for the county of Somerset. Outpatient clinics are run at Taunton and Yeovil hospitals. All categories of solid cancer or malignant tumours (with the exception of paediatrics and the rarer cancers such as testicular, sarcoma and primary brain) are seen by the department. Most radiotherapy treatments are delivered within the Beacon Centre (Musgrove's cancer centre). Brachytherapy remains at Bristol.</div>
<div>
<p>Chemotherapy is delivered both on a day care (at Taunton and Yeovil) and inpatient basis (Taunton only). Outreach chemotherapy clinics are currently held at Bridgwater and Deane Barton Community Unit. Inpatient beds for specialist oncology treatments and side effect management are on the <a href="http://www.musgroveparkhospital.nhs.uk/wards-and-departments/wards/beacon/" title="Beacon">Beacon Ward</a> within Musgrove Park Hospital.</p>
</div>
<div>For further information, please don’t hesitate to contact us via Beacon Day Unit on 01823 342296.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
